<subSubSection id="6DE165012504FF85FF451002FB87FE2B" pageId="17" pageNumber="1632" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="2544368A2504FF85FF451002FB87FE2B" blockId="17.[178,1085,336,388]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1632">Etymology: The specific epithet is the past participle of the Latin verb inflare (to inflate) and alludes to the large basal portion of the internal structure of the aedeagus.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6DE165012504FF85FF4510C6FEA8FB7C" pageId="17" pageNumber="1632" type="description">
<paragraph id="2544368A2504FF85FF4510C6FCF3FE4A" blockId="17.[178,1086,404,485]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1632">
Description: Small species; body length 6.0 mm; length of forebody 
<quantity id="E2039B6F2504FF85FC1010C6FBA8FE05" box="[999,1082,404,426]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="17" pageNumber="1632" unit="mm" value="2.5">2.5 mm</quantity>
. Habitus as in 
<figureCitation id="BDC02A0F2504FF85FEB510E3FE1DFE68" box="[322,399,433,455]" captionStart="Figs 36-43" captionStartId="16.[178,218,1512,1532]" captionTargetBox="[187,1073,212,1485]" captionTargetId="figure-66@16.[178,1085,212,1497]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figs 36-43: Lathrobium inflatum nov.sp.: (36) habitus; (37) forebody; (38) male sternite VII; (39) male sternite VIII; (40-41) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (42) dorso-apical portion of aedeagus in lateral view; (43) apical portion of aedeagus in dorsal view. Scale bars: 36-37: 1.0 mm; 38-43: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303087" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303087/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="1632">Fig. 36</figureCitation>
. Coloration: body reddish-brown with the abdominal segments V-VII somewhat darker; legs pale yellowish-brown; antennae reddish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2544368A2504FF85FF4510A6FF74FDD0" blockId="17.[178,1086,500,639]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1632">
Head (
<figureCitation id="BDC02A0F2504FF85FF0010A6FED3FDA5" box="[247,321,500,522]" captionStart="Figs 36-43" captionStartId="16.[178,218,1512,1532]" captionTargetBox="[187,1073,212,1485]" captionTargetId="figure-66@16.[178,1085,212,1497]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figs 36-43: Lathrobium inflatum nov.sp.: (36) habitus; (37) forebody; (38) male sternite VII; (39) male sternite VIII; (40-41) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (42) dorso-apical portion of aedeagus in lateral view; (43) apical portion of aedeagus in dorsal view. Scale bars: 36-37: 1.0 mm; 38-43: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303087" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303087/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="1632">Fig. 37</figureCitation>
) approximately as long as broad; punctation moderately coarse and rather sparse, interstices distinctly broader than diameter of punctures, with shallow microreticulation. Eyes small, weakly convex, and composed of approximately 25 ommatidia, approximately one fourth as long as postocular region in dorsal view. Antenna 
<quantity id="E2039B6F2504FF85FC19131EFBACFDCE" box="[1006,1086,588,610]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="17" pageNumber="1632" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
long.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2544368A2504FF85FF4513DDFC3CFD6E" blockId="17.[178,1086,654,705]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1632">
Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="BDC02A0F2504FF85FED413DCFEFFFD0B" box="[291,365,654,676]" captionStart="Figs 36-43" captionStartId="16.[178,218,1512,1532]" captionTargetBox="[187,1073,212,1485]" captionTargetId="figure-66@16.[178,1085,212,1497]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figs 36-43: Lathrobium inflatum nov.sp.: (36) habitus; (37) forebody; (38) male sternite VII; (39) male sternite VIII; (40-41) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (42) dorso-apical portion of aedeagus in lateral view; (43) apical portion of aedeagus in dorsal view. Scale bars: 36-37: 1.0 mm; 38-43: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303087" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303087/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="1632">Fig. 37</figureCitation>
) 
<quantity id="E2039B6F2504FF85FE8C13DCFE47FD0B" box="[379,469,654,676]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" pageId="17" pageNumber="1632" unit="mm" value="1.25">1.25 mm</quantity>
long and approximately as broad as head; punctation similar to that of head, but distinctly denser; impunctate midline moderately broad.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2544368A2504FF85FF451383FDCAFCAB" blockId="17.[178,1086,721,772]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1632">
Elytra (
<figureCitation id="BDC02A0F2504FF85FEF61383FEDFFD48" box="[257,333,721,743]" captionStart="Figs 36-43" captionStartId="16.[178,218,1512,1532]" captionTargetBox="[187,1073,212,1485]" captionTargetId="figure-66@16.[178,1085,212,1497]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figs 36-43: Lathrobium inflatum nov.sp.: (36) habitus; (37) forebody; (38) male sternite VII; (39) male sternite VIII; (40-41) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (42) dorso-apical portion of aedeagus in lateral view; (43) apical portion of aedeagus in dorsal view. Scale bars: 36-37: 1.0 mm; 38-43: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303087" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303087/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="1632">Fig. 37</figureCitation>
) moderately short, 0.65 times as long as pronotum; punctation fine and shallow. Hind wings completely reduced.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2544368A2504FF85FF451241FEBBFCCB" blockId="17.[178,1086,787,868]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1632">Abdomen slender, but distinctly broader than elytra; punctation very fine and very dense; interstices with distinct microreticulation; posterior margin of tergite VII without palisade fringe.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2544368A2504FF85FF301226FEF8FB01" blockId="17.[178,1086,883,1198]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1632">
: protarsomeres I-IV strongly dilated; tergite VIII with weakly convex posterior margin; sternites III-VI unmodified; sternite VII (
<figureCitation id="BDC02A0F2504FF85FD7F12C2FD41FC09" box="[648,723,912,934]" captionStart="Figs 36-43" captionStartId="16.[178,218,1512,1532]" captionTargetBox="[187,1073,212,1485]" captionTargetId="figure-66@16.[178,1085,212,1497]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figs 36-43: Lathrobium inflatum nov.sp.: (36) habitus; (37) forebody; (38) male sternite VII; (39) male sternite VIII; (40-41) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (42) dorso-apical portion of aedeagus in lateral view; (43) apical portion of aedeagus in dorsal view. Scale bars: 36-37: 1.0 mm; 38-43: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303087" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303087/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="1632">Fig. 38</figureCitation>
) strongly transverse and with shallow postero-median impression, posterior margin weakly concave, pubescence unmodified; sternite VIII (
<figureCitation id="BDC02A0F2504FF85FE861299FE29FC4E" box="[369,443,971,993]" captionStart="Figs 36-43" captionStartId="16.[178,218,1512,1532]" captionTargetBox="[187,1073,212,1485]" captionTargetId="figure-66@16.[178,1085,212,1497]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figs 36-43: Lathrobium inflatum nov.sp.: (36) habitus; (37) forebody; (38) male sternite VII; (39) male sternite VIII; (40-41) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (42) dorso-apical portion of aedeagus in lateral view; (43) apical portion of aedeagus in dorsal view. Scale bars: 36-37: 1.0 mm; 38-43: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303087" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303087/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="1632">Fig. 39</figureCitation>
) weakly oblong, pubescence unmodified, posterior excision Vshaped and moderately deep; aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="BDC02A0F2504FF85FDA412BAFD56FC51" box="[595,708,1000,1022]" captionStart="Figs 36-43" captionStartId="16.[178,218,1512,1532]" captionTargetBox="[187,1073,212,1485]" captionTargetId="figure-66@16.[178,1085,212,1497]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figs 36-43: Lathrobium inflatum nov.sp.: (36) habitus; (37) forebody; (38) male sternite VII; (39) male sternite VIII; (40-41) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (42) dorso-apical portion of aedeagus in lateral view; (43) apical portion of aedeagus in dorsal view. Scale bars: 36-37: 1.0 mm; 38-43: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303087" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303087/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="1632">Figs 40-43</figureCitation>
) 1.0 mm long; ventral process symmetric, slender and subapically weakly curved in lateral view, and apically acute; dorsal plate with long, stout, strongly sclerotized, and apically acute apical portion and with long, slender, lamellate, and weakly sclerotized basal portion; internal sac with two sclerotized structures, one of them moderately long, slender, apically acute, and basally bifid and the other basally very large, apically extending into a long, slender, strongly curved, asymmetric spine.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2544368A2504FF85FF3015ECFEA8FB7C" blockId="17.[199,314,1213,1235]" box="[199,314,1213,1235]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1632">: unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6DE165012504FF85FF4515B0FCE0FA24" pageId="17" pageNumber="1632" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="2544368A2504FF85FF4515B0FCE0FA24" blockId="17.[178,1086,1250,1419]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1632">
Comparative notes: Based on the similar external characters, the shape and chaetotaxy of the male sternite VII and VIII, and particularly on the similarly derived morphology of the aedeagus (internal sac with a basally strongly inflated sclerotized structure), 
<taxonomicName id="E2FB4D092504FF85FED51469FE01FAFF" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2013" box="[290,403,1338,1360]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="1632" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inflatum">
<emphasis id="178FEA982504FF85FED51469FE01FAFF" box="[290,403,1338,1360]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1632">L. inflatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
undoubtedly belongs to the 
<taxonomicName id="E2FB4D092504FF85FD481469FCB5FAFF" authorityName="HERMAN" authorityYear="2003" box="[703,807,1339,1360]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="1632" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinense">
<emphasis id="178FEA982504FF85FD481469FCB5FAFF" box="[703,807,1339,1360]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1632">L. sinense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. In external characters, it is practically indistinguishable from the similar 
<taxonomicName id="E2FB4D092504FF85FD02140BFCE4FAC1" authorityName="WATANABE" authorityYear="2001" box="[757,886,1368,1390]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="1632" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nikkoense">
<emphasis id="178FEA982504FF85FD02140BFCE4FAC1" box="[757,886,1368,1390]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1632">L. nikkoense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs by the completely different shapes of the internal structures of the aedeagus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6DE165012504FF85FF4514C8FE97FA45" pageId="17" pageNumber="1632" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="2544368A2504FF85FF4514C8FE97FA45" blockId="17.[178,1085,1434,1515]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1632">
Distribution: The 
<typeStatus id="FA4088282504FF85FE2314C9FD92FA1F" box="[468,512,1435,1456]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1632">type</typeStatus>
locality is situated at the foot of Hotaka-san (
